{
  "$comment": "Neutral shipped <fcntl.h> (POSIX) — c14d (linux) + c15c (macOS). The first VARIADIC-extern consumer (c14c): open/fcntl are variadic (open(path,flags,...); fcntl(fd,cmd,...) passes &flock as a vararg → struct flock is NOT in the signature). The O_*/F_* VALUES are interop-CRITICAL (a wrong flag mis-opens/mis-locks) and DIVERGE heavily between Linux (asm-generic/fcntl.h) and macOS (xnu/bsd/sys/fcntl.h) — every divergent one carries per-format `variants` (verified against both header sets): O_CREAT 64/512, O_EXCL 128/2048, O_TRUNC 512/1024, O_APPEND 1024/8, O_NONBLOCK 2048/4, O_NOFOLLOW 131072/256, O_DIRECTORY 65536/1048576, O_CLOEXEC 524288/16777216; the fcntl lock cmds F_GETLK 5/7, F_SETLK 6/8, F_SETLKW 7/9; the lock TYPES F_RDLCK 0/1, F_WRLCK 1/3 (★ macOS reorders these — F_UNLCK=2 happens to agree). O_RDONLY/WRONLY/RDWR (0/1/2), F_DUPFD/GETFD/SETFD/GETFL/SETFL (0..4), F_UNLCK (2), FD_CLOEXEC (1) AGREE → flat. O_LARGEFILE is a 64-bit no-op (0) on both (Linux 64-bit defines it 0; macOS has no LFS toggle and SQLite's own fallback is 0). O_TMPFILE is LINUX-ONLY → elf-only variant (not injected on macho; a macho reference fails loud). `struct flock` DIVERGES: Linux {short l_type,l_whence; off_t l_start,l_len; pid_t l_pid}=32B vs macOS REORDERED {off_t l_start,l_len; pid_t l_pid; short l_type,l_whence}=24B → per-format struct variants. arm64/x86_64 agree within each OS (fixed-width fields). Gated availableObjectFormats:[elf,macho]. | c106 pe: library.pe=msvcrt.dll; open/fcntl per-symbol gated [elf,macho] (the c101 EAGER-IMPORT LAW - msvcrt exports _open not open); pe arms on O_CREAT/O_EXCL/O_TRUNC/O_APPEND (ucrt _O_ 0x100/0x400/0x200/0x8) + the 13 MSVC _O_* pe-only variants (ucrt 10.0.26100.0; _O_WTEXT 0x10000/_O_U8TEXT 0x40000 = shell.c _setmode); O_RDONLY/WRONLY/RDWR 0/1/2 coincide; POSIX-only O_* have no pe arm; F_* flats inject dead on pe (use reaches the gated fcntl()).",
